{"title": "Your turn: define your MVP", "userText": "na
", "aiResponse": "I apologize, but it seems like no details were provided about your Minimum Viable Product (MVP). Could you share more information about the features, user stories, or the problem you're trying to solve? Without any context, I can't provide meaningful feedback or guidance. I'm keen to help you refine your MVP and ensure it's focused and valuable.", "description": "Go through your user story map and chose the steps and details that will be in your MVP.

Ask yourself, 'Do I really need this feature to test my core value proposition?' Write your MVP below as bullet points or a short paragraph."}

{"title": "Now it's your turn: Map out the big picture", "userText": "na", "aiResponse": "I apologize, but it seems like no activities were actually shared in your message. Could you please provide the list of main activities for your user story map? I'd be happy to review them and provide constructive feedback to help you develop a clear, user-focused map.", "description": "What are the main activities your user will perform in your product to achieve their goals?

Write them down on separate sticky notes in the order they would happen, so you can move them around as you identify more activities.

Then add the activities below."}

{"title": "Now it's your turn: Visualise what your user can do and how they feel once the struggle is resolved.", "userText": "Mark just received a report showing him exactly what in his daily workflow can be automated and how. He’s very excited to implement these tools and become more efficient while also reducing the likelihood of error in his and his team’s work.
", "aiResponse": "Brilliant start! I like how you've captured Mark's emotional response and the tangible outcome of his solution. To make this even sharper, consider specifying what type of workflow Mark is in (e.g., marketing operations, software development) and perhaps one specific automation that will make a big difference for him.

Visualising what your user can do and how they feel once their struggle is resolved helps you come up with better solutions for them!", "description": "On the piece of paper, draw what your user can do and how they feel once the struggle is resolved. Then write it down in a few sentences below."}

{"title": "Your turn: define your MVP", "userText": "Search FUnction, this way the Reader can find what they are looking for, without having an organized blogger or city/country list/overview.", "aiResponse": "I'm happy to provide feedback, but it seems like you've only shared the title of your MVP feature. Could you elaborate a bit more on the specific details of this search function? What exactly will users be able to search for, and what are the core capabilities you're envisioning? A bit more context would help me provide more targeted advice about your MVP approach. 

I'm keen to understand the scope and purpose of your search functionality. What problem are you solving for your users with this search feature?", "description": "Go through your user story map and chose the steps and details that will be in your MVP.

Ask yourself, 'Do I really need this feature to test my core value proposition?' Write your MVP below as bullet points or a short paragraph."}

{"title": "Now it's your turn: Map out the details", "userText": "I think I already provided the details. Not sure, what to put", "aiResponse": "I apologize, but it seems like you haven't shared the details of your user story map yet. Could you please provide the details you've identified? I'll be happy to review them and offer constructive feedback to help you refine your user story map. Remember, good details typically start with an action verb and describe specific tasks a user would perform.", "description": "What are the details under each step that needs to be built? Go through all the steps and break them down into specific details. It's okay if your list gets a bit long, you'll prioritise them soon.

For now, capture everything the user or app does in each step. Use separate sticky notes for each detail.

Then add the details below."}

{"title": "Now it's your turn: Sketch all the moments inbetween", "userText": "Cindy finds a blogger web app, where she can find all information at one spot, expereiences from different bloggers, with direct link to google maps, so she does not have to manually add them to her google. It makes her so happy, to save this time, researching normally stresses her a lil out.
Now she has everything in one spot and they are up to date. I can choose how recent the data should be.", "aiResponse": "Your description is a bit broad and could benefit from more specific details. While I like that you've identified Cindy's pain point of research stress, try to break down her journey more precisely. What specific steps does she take in the web app? How exactly does she navigate from finding information to saving time? A more detailed walkthrough would help clarify the user's experience.

Creating these steps of a storyboard helps you envision how your product will help your user!", "description": "On the piece of paper, sketch all the moments that lead the user from the initial struggling moment to their happy ending. Show how your solution helps them get there. Then write it down in a few sentences below."}

